MALACAÑANG MANILA

PROCLAMATION NO. 124

ESTABLISHING AS ABASIG-MATOGDON WATERSHED FOREST RESERVE CERTAIN PARCELS OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN SITUATED IN THE MUNICIPALITIES OF LABO AND SAN VICENTE, PROVINCE OF CAMARINES NORTE, ISLAND OF LUZON, PHILIPPINES.

Upon recommendation of the Secretary of Natural Resources and by virtue of the powers vested in me by law, I, CORAZON C. AQUINO, President of the Philippines, do hereby withdraw from entry, sale, disposition or settlement and set aside for watershed and other ecological enhancement purposes, subject to private rights, if there by any, and to the operations of the previous proclamations reserving any portion thereof for specific purposes, the parcels of public domain located in the municipalities of Labo and San Vicente, province of Camarines Norte, Island of Luzon, more particularly described as follows:

From BBM No. 5 of Labo, Camarines Norte, it being S 75º00′ E; 420.00 meters to a point marked “1” on the Map WR-58:

